The paper deals with the problem of detecting Android malware, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed approach involves building Bayesian classification models using static code analysis, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the evaluation of the models, which involves experimentation and analysis, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE) and data structures (cs.DS).
